OL,3,CSpring on pause: Arctic blast brings
OL,4,Csnow risk and a bitter chill across
OL,5,Cthe UK
OL,7,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,8,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,9,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,10,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,12,FWhen is the coldest part of the week?
OL,14,FTomorrow is likely to be the coldest
OL,15,Fday of the week with temperatures
OL,16,Fstruggling into single figures.
OL,18,FIn the strong northerly wind,
OL,19,Ftemperatures will feel far lower than
OL,20,Feven the single digits that you see on
OL,21,Fthe map.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1774379485
OL,3,CSpring on pause: Arctic blast brings
OL,4,Csnow risk and a bitter chill across
OL,5,Cthe UK
OL,7,FAs the wind eases somewhat and backs
OL,8,Faround to a more northwesterly
OL,9,Fdirection on Thursday, it will feel a
OL,10,Flot less raw and temperatures should
OL,11,Fclimb a degree or so.
OL,13,FBy Friday, we should be just about
OL,14,Fback up into double figures in a
OL,15,Fwesterly airflow which, whilst not
OL,16,Fexactly warm, is certainly less biting
OL,17,Fthan one that plunges straight down
OL,18,Ffrom the Arctic!
OL,20,FIs this unusual for March?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1774379485
OL,3,CSpring on pause: Arctic blast brings
OL,4,Csnow risk and a bitter chill across
OL,5,Cthe UK
OL,7,FNot at all.
OL,9,FMarch is a month of contrasts ` and
OL,10,Fthis is a classic example.
OL,12,FWe can swing from warm days to very
OL,13,Fchilly nights, and from lovely
OL,14,Fsunshine to wintry showers very
OL,15,Fquickly before the weather gradually
OL,16,Fsettles down as we head further into
OL,17,Fspring.
OL,19,FAny other weather hazards to watch out
OL,20,Ffor?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1774379485
OL,3,CSpring on pause: Arctic blast brings
OL,4,Csnow risk and a bitter chill across
OL,5,Cthe UK
OL,7,FYes ` it's not just the cold. Heavy
OL,8,Frain across northern England (notably
OL,9,FCumbria and Lancashire) through this
OL,10,Fafternoon could give some tricky
OL,11,Fdriving conditions.
OL,13,FIce too could be an issue for some as
OL,14,Ftemperatures fall away sharply
OL,15,Fovernight. And it's going to be windy
OL,16,Fof course with wind speeds widely 20-
OL,17,F30mph but up to 50mph in exposed areas.
OL,19,FWill it stay cold for long?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1774379485
OL,3,CSpring on pause: Arctic blast brings
OL,4,Csnow risk and a bitter chill across
OL,5,Cthe UK
OL,7,FThe coldest conditions through
OL,8,Ftomorrow shouldn't last too long and
OL,9,Fbe back to around average (10-12C).
OL,11,FAlthough there isn't any sign yet of a
OL,12,Freturn to the warm sunshine of last
OL,13,Fweek, with the Easter holidays fast
OL,14,Fapproaching, largely dry conditions
OL,15,Fwith decent sunshine will be more than
OL,16,Facceptable to parents everywhere -
OL,17,Feven if it still feels a bit chilly!
OL,19,FSo keep the winter woolies handy this
OL,20,Fweek - but don't despair.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
